{"page_content": "![](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/_assets/3137b1a864c689786cac76b3def62dd1/Assets/img/default-banner.jpg)\n\n# Heavy Vehicle Owners and Operators\n\nHeavy vehicle owners and operators must be familiar with and comply with the rules governing road transportation of goods and passengers.\n\n## Heavy vehicles covered\n\n- A road vehicle with a gross vehicle weight rating (GVWR) of 4,500 kg or more\n- A combination of road vehicles with a gross combination weight rating of 4,500 kg or more\n- A tow truck\n- A road vehicle transporting dangerous substances requiring the display of safety marks\n- A bus\n- A minibus\n\n## Obligations regarding heavy vehicles\n\nHeavy vehicle owners and operators also have many responsibilities, some of which they share. These responsibilities concern, in particular, the following subjects:\n\n### Owners\n\n- Mechanical maintenance of their vehicles\n\n### Operators\n\n- Circle checks\n- Load securement standards\n- Load and size limits\n- Transportation of dangerous substances\n- Special travel permits\n\nLast update: May 17, 2022\n\n## Safety first, on the road and online\n\nWe are committed to protecting your personal information and privacy. That's why, when we collect data, we follow a [Policy on Privacy](https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/policies/privacy) that is responsible and transparent. By continuing to browse without modifying your preferences, you accept the use of cookies.\n\nEdit settingsAcceptReject\n\nDÃ©tection du zoom", "metadata": {"title": "Heavy Vehicle Owners and Operators - SAAQ", "description": "Heavy vehicle owners and operators must be familiar and comply with the rules governing road transportation. ", "url": "https://saaq.gouv.qc.ca/en/transportation-goods/owners-operators", "language": "en", "keywords": "heavy vehicle, heavy truck, owner, operator, truck, trucking, road transportation, hvoo", "robots": null, "og_title": "Heavy Vehicle Owners and Operators", "og_description": "Heavy vehicle owners and oper